'''Breathing''' refers to the shifting of  [[angle of view]] of a [[lens (optics)|lens]]   when changing the  [[focus (optics)|focus]]. Some (often higher quality) lenses are designed to lessen the degree of this effect. Lens breathing does not prevent one from [[racking focus]] or [[follow focus|following focus]] with this lens, but it lessens the desirability of any type of focus adjustment, since it noticeably changes the composition of the shot.<ref>{{cite web|title=SAMPLE - LENS BREATHING|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bIrJUFtYxiQ|publisher=hdslr35 on Youtube|accessdate=13 June 2014}}</ref>  This is not to be confused with the suction and expulsion of air from within the lens as its internal volume changes.
